---
const principles = [
  {
    kanji: "心",
    title: "Kokoro",
    subtitle: "Heart & Mind",
    description:
      "Cultivate mental clarity and emotional balance through focused breathing and meditation integrated into every movement.",
  },
  {
    kanji: "技",
    title: "Waza",
    subtitle: "Technique",
    description:
      "Master precise body mechanics and movement patterns refined over centuries of martial arts tradition.",
  },
  {
    kanji: "体",
    title: "Karada",
    subtitle: "Body",
    description:
      "Develop functional strength, flexibility, and coordination that serves you in every aspect of daily life.",
  },
]
---

<section id="philosophy" class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-background">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
      <!-- Left column -->
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm tracking-[0.3em] uppercase text-accent mb-4">
          Philosophy
        </p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold leading-tight text-foreground text-balance">
          Discipline of the Body, Stillness of the Mind
        </h2>
      </div>

      <!-- Right column -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          Taiso, meaning "body conditioning" in Japanese, is a holistic practice that draws from the rich traditions of martial arts. It is not merely exercise—it is a way of cultivating awareness, balance, and inner strength through deliberate, mindful movement.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
          Rooted in the principles of Judo and traditional Japanese physical culture, Taiso develops flexibility, coordination, and mental clarity. Each session is a journey toward deeper understanding of your own body.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Three principles -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mt-20">
      {principles.map((principle) => (
        <div class="group border border-border rounded-sm p-8 transition-colors hover:bg-secondary">
          <span class="text-5xl text-accent opacity-60 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity">
            {principle.kanji}
          </span>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-foreground mt-4">
            {principle.title}
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm tracking-wide text-accent mt-1 mb-3">
            {principle.subtitle}
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
            {principle.description}
          </p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
